WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: I.V.M.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.640
[Amit Varma]: The purpose of the organization was to set protocols by which mail could be exchanged

00:00:35.640 --> 00:00:38.640
[Amit Varma]: between the 22 different nations that were part of it.

00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:42.360
[Amit Varma]: You could say to create the HTTP of the offline world.

00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:46.880
[Amit Varma]: As the 19th century drew to an end, one of the problems it faced was how to enable a

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:52.240
[Amit Varma]: person in one country to pay the return postage for a letter from another country.

00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:57.200
[Amit Varma]: For example, an Italian immigrant to America might send a letter to Italy to his aged parents

00:00:57.200 --> 00:01:01.920
[Amit Varma]: and may want to enclose a self-addressed stamped envelope so that they can reply without having

00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:02.920
[Amit Varma]: to buy stamps.

00:01:02.920 --> 00:01:06.880
[Amit Varma]: But obviously, American stamps will not work in Italy and he can't buy Italian stamps in

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:07.880
[Amit Varma]: America.

00:01:07.880 --> 00:01:08.880
[Amit Varma]: So what to do?

00:01:08.880 --> 00:01:13.240
[Amit Varma]: The Universal Postal Union came up with a clever solution in 1904.

00:01:13.240 --> 00:01:17.640
[Amit Varma]: This was basically an international stamp called the International Reply Coupon or an

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:22.440
[Amit Varma]: IRC, which would be valid anywhere and which could be purchased in any of these countries

00:01:22.440 --> 00:01:25.200
[Amit Varma]: for a fixed amount of local currency.

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:30.680
[Amit Varma]: The system works superbly and aspiring writers of a certain vintage may remember that as

00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:36.280
[Amit Varma]: recently as the 1990s, publications abroad would ask you to submit your writing to them

00:01:36.280 --> 00:01:40.760
[Amit Varma]: with an International Reply Coupon so that the polite rejection letter they would send

00:01:40.760 --> 00:01:42.960
[Amit Varma]: you would be at your cost.

00:01:42.960 --> 00:01:48.240
[Amit Varma]: Now the Universal Postal Union is an upstanding organization and not the subject of this episode,

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:51.800
[Amit Varma]: but their IRCs set in motion an interesting scheme.

00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:55.800
[Amit Varma]: Now remember, these coupons could be bought across all these countries for a set amount

00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:57.400
[Amit Varma]: of local currency.

00:01:57.400 --> 00:02:00.000
[Amit Varma]: But what happened when currencies fluctuated?

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.480
[Amit Varma]: An IRC would automatically become cheaper in one country than another.

00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:08.260
[Amit Varma]: And currencies did fluctuate wildly because of World War I.

00:02:08.260 --> 00:02:14.240
[Amit Varma]: As the war came to an end in 1919, an Italian immigrant in Boston received some International

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:16.900
[Amit Varma]: Reply Coupons in a mail from Spain.

00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:19.500
[Amit Varma]: He realized the opportunity for arbitrage here.

00:02:19.500 --> 00:02:26.720
[Amit Varma]: He calculated that if he bought $1 worth of IRCs in Rome, it would be worth $3.30 in Boston,

00:02:26.720 --> 00:02:29.240
[Amit Varma]: a profit of 230%.

00:02:29.240 --> 00:02:33.960
[Amit Varma]: Other countries had even more devalued currencies, such as Austria, and he could make even more

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:34.960
[Amit Varma]: money there.

00:02:34.960 --> 00:02:36.360
[Amit Varma]: So he formulated a business plan.

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:40.920
[Amit Varma]: Buy IRCs cheap in Europe, make a profit selling them in the US.

00:02:40.920 --> 00:02:43.160
[Amit Varma]: This was an entirely legitimate business plan.

00:02:43.160 --> 00:02:46.400
[Amit Varma]: There's nothing wrong with buying cheap and selling expensive.

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:50.760
[Amit Varma]: Our man needed money for this though, and he had already burnt his fingers with various

00:02:50.760 --> 00:02:54.600
[Amit Varma]: failed enterprises in the 15 years since he'd left Italy.

00:02:54.600 --> 00:02:58.400
[Amit Varma]: No one was going to lend him large sums of money, but he figured he could get the capital

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:00.720
[Amit Varma]: he needed from small investors.

00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:06.680
[Amit Varma]: He formed a company called the Securities Exchange Company, the SEC, which sounds respectable,

00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:12.000
[Amit Varma]: and advertised a scheme promising that anyone who invested money with him would get a 50%

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.120
[Amit Varma]: return in 45 days.

00:03:14.120 --> 00:03:15.880
[Amit Varma]: This is a mad rate of return.

00:03:15.880 --> 00:03:21.560
[Amit Varma]: He even turned a few of his initial investors into agents, giving them 10% of whatever investments

00:03:21.560 --> 00:03:23.120
[Amit Varma]: they got in.

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:27.120
[Amit Varma]: Everyone who invested automatically became an evangelist of the company, as they rationalized

00:03:27.120 --> 00:03:29.920
[Amit Varma]: their investment and began recommending it to others.

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:35.160
[Amit Varma]: Over time, as initial batches of investors actually received that 50% interest, they

00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:36.160
[Amit Varma]: became bhakts.

00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:40.960
[Amit Varma]: They often reinvested their money while selling property to gather other funds to invest.

00:03:40.960 --> 00:03:44.000
[Amit Varma]: Old women invested their savings of a lifetime.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.360
[Amit Varma]: Early men mortgaged their homes to add to their savings that they'd already invested.

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:53.680
[Amit Varma]: In February 1920, the total investments in this scheme were only $5,000.

00:03:53.680 --> 00:03:55.680
[Amit Varma]: A month later, $30,000.

00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:58.200
[Amit Varma]: By May, over $400,000.

00:03:58.200 --> 00:04:00.520
[Amit Varma]: By July, it was bringing in millions.

00:04:00.520 --> 00:04:04.840
[Amit Varma]: Once newspaper coverage started in late July, it started bringing in a quarter of a million

00:04:04.840 --> 00:04:06.600
[Amit Varma]: dollars a day.

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:11.600
[Amit Varma]: Estimates of how much money was invested in the scheme vary from 15 to 20 million dollars,

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:17.960
[Amit Varma]: and 20 million in those days would be around 250 million today, close to 2000 crore rupees.

00:04:17.960 --> 00:04:23.320
[Amit Varma]: The thing is, none of this money was actually invested in IRCs.

00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:28.240
[Amit Varma]: Our enterprising entrepreneur found it hard to get hold of IRCs bought in Europe and found

00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:29.800
[Amit Varma]: no way to sell them in the US.

00:04:29.800 --> 00:04:35.320
[Amit Varma]: Also, the total number of international reply coupons available worldwide was a fraction

00:04:35.320 --> 00:04:38.040
[Amit Varma]: of the number that the invested money would buy.

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:40.080
[Amit Varma]: So the scheme clearly could not work.

00:04:40.080 --> 00:04:42.560
[Amit Varma]: How did the whole enterprise work then?

00:04:42.560 --> 00:04:43.560
[Amit Varma]: Simple.

00:04:43.560 --> 00:04:48.240
[Amit Varma]: The securities exchange company basically paid out its investors from the money of later

00:04:48.240 --> 00:04:49.240
[Amit Varma]: investors.

00:04:49.240 --> 00:04:52.720
[Amit Varma]: Put simply, the first batch would be paid out by the money of the second batch, the

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:55.040
[Amit Varma]: second batch by the money of the third batch.

00:04:55.040 --> 00:04:59.960
[Amit Varma]: And as long as the investments kept increasing, as they did because of the high praise by

00:04:59.960 --> 00:05:02.840
[Amit Varma]: earlier payouts, all would be well.

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:07.280
[Amit Varma]: But at some point, this would have to end and the whole scheme would collapse, as this

00:05:07.280 --> 00:05:08.880
[Amit Varma]: one did.

00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:13.520
[Amit Varma]: This sort of fraud, robbing Peter to pay Paul, goes back through the ages.

00:05:13.520 --> 00:05:18.440
[Amit Varma]: But in the popular imagination, they are now known by the name of this Italian immigrant

00:05:18.440 --> 00:05:25.520
[Amit Varma]: who founded the securities exchange company, Carlo Pietro Giovanni Guglielmi Tebaldo Ponzi,

00:05:25.520 --> 00:05:41.880
[Unknown]: Charles Ponzi.

